sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Spark Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Spark Operator Controller<br/>8080/TCP metrics
    participant SparkSubmit as spark-submit<br/>(local process)
    participant Driver as Spark Driver Pod
    participant Executors as Spark Executor Pods
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 1: SparkApplication Submission and Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. kubectl apply SparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. Admission webhook (validate + default)<br/>HTTPS/9443, API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: CR validated and defaulted
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR created

    K8sAPI->>Controller: 3. Watch event: new SparkApplication
    Controller->>SparkSubmit: 4. Invoke spark-submit<br/>(local process exec)
    SparkSubmit->>K8sAPI: 5. Create driver pod<br/>HTTPS/6443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 6. Mutate driver pod<br/>(25+ mutations: env, volumes, scheduling)<br/>HTTPS/9443, API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Pod mutated

    Driver->>K8sAPI: 7. Request executor pods<br/>HTTPS/6443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutate executor pods<br/>HTTPS/9443, API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Pods mutated

    Driver->>Executors: 8. Spark RPC communication<br/>7078/TCP driver-rpc<br/>7079/TCP block-manager<br/>HTTP, No encryption
    Executors-->>Driver: Task results

    Controller->>K8sAPI: 9. Update SparkApplication status<br/>HTTPS/6443, ServiceAccount token

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 2: ScheduledSparkApplication

    Controller->>Controller: Cron trigger fires
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create SparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, ServiceAccount token
    Note right of Controller: Follows Flow 1 steps 2-9
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Enforce concurrency policy<br/>Manage history (cleanup old runs)

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 3: Spark Connect Server

    User->>K8sAPI: Create SparkConnect CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer token
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: new SparkConnect
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap (executor template)<br/>HTTPS/6443
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create server Pod<br/>HTTPS/6443
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create server Service<br/>HTTPS/6443

    participant Client as Spark Connect Client
    Client->>Driver: Connect to server<br/>gRPC/15002, No encryption
    Driver->>Executors: Spark RPC<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP

    Note over User,Prometheus: Monitoring

    Prometheus->>Controller: Scrape /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080, No auth
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Application metrics<br/>(submit count, execution times, executor metrics)
